If the value of the determinant $$\left| {\matrix{
   a &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; b &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; c  \cr 

 } } \right|$$ is positive, where a $$\ne$$ b $$\ne$$ c, then the value of abc

explanation:
Let $$\Delta  = \left| {\matrix{
   a &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; b &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; c  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = a(bc - 1) - 1(c - 1) + 1(1 - b)$$<br><br>$$ = abc - a - b - c + 2$$<br><br>$$ \because $$ $$\Delta  &gt; 0$$<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ $$abc - a - b - c + 2 &gt; 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow abc + 2 &gt; a + b + c$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow abc + 2 &gt; 3{(abc)^{1/3}}$$<br><br>[$$\because$$ a $$\ne$$ b $$\ne$$ c $$\Rightarrow$$ AM of a, b, c &gt; GM of $$a,b,c \Rightarrow {{a + b + c} \over 3} &gt; {(abc)^{1/3}}$$ $$ \Rightarrow a + b + c &gt; 3{(abc)^{1/3}}$$]<br><br>Now, let $$x = {(abc)^{1/3}}$$, then we have<br><br>$${x^3} + 2 &gt; 3x$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {x^3} - 3x + 2 &gt; 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {(x - 1)^2}(x + 2) &gt; 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x + 2 &gt; 0$$ [$$\because$$ $${(x - 1)^2} &gt; 0$$]<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x &gt;  - 2$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {(abc)^{1/3}} &gt;  - 2$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow abc &gt;  - 8$$

