 } } \right|$$<br><br>On taking common ($$\alpha$$ $$-$$ $$\beta$$) and ($$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\alpha$$) from R<sub>1</sub> and R<sub>2</sub> respectively, we get<br><br>$$ = (\alpha  - \beta )(\beta  - \gamma )\left| {\matrix{
