What is the determinant of the matrix $$\left( {\matrix{
   x &amp; y &amp; {y + z}  \cr 
   z &amp; x &amp; {z + x}  \cr 
   y &amp; z &amp; {x + y}  \cr 

 } } \right)$$ ?

explanation:
We have,<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   x &amp; y &amp; {y + z}  \cr 
   z &amp; x &amp; {z + x}  \cr 
   y &amp; z &amp; {x + y}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>R<sub>1</sub> $$\to$$ R<sub>1</sub> + R<sub>2</sub> + R<sub>3</sub><br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   {x + y + z} &amp; {x + y + z} &amp; {2(x + y + z)}  \cr 
   z &amp; x &amp; {z + x}  \cr 
   y &amp; z &amp; {x + y}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = (x + y + z)\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 2  \cr 
   z &amp; x &amp; {z + x}  \cr 
   y &amp; z &amp; {x + y}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>C<sub>2</sub> $$\to$$ C<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ C<sub>1</sub> and C<sub>3</sub> $$\to$$ C<sub>3</sub> $$-$$ 2C<sub>1</sub><br><br>$$ = (x + y + z)\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   z &amp; {x - z} &amp; {x - z}  \cr 
   y &amp; {z - y} &amp; {x - y}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = (x + y + z)[1(x - z)(x - y) - (x - z)(z - y)]$$<br><br>$$ = (x + y + z)[(x - z)(x - y - z + y)]$$<br><br>$$ = (x + y + z)(x - z)(x - z)$$<br><br>$$ = (x + y + z){(z - x)^2}$$

