What are the values of x that satisfy the equation $$\left| {\matrix{
   x &amp; 0 &amp; 2  \cr 
   {2x} &amp; 2 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right| + \left| {\matrix{
   {3x} &amp; 0 &amp; 2  \cr 
   {{x^2}} &amp; 2 &amp; 1  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$ ?

explanation:
Given equation,<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   x &amp; 0 &amp; 2  \cr 
   {2x} &amp; 2 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right| + \left| {\matrix{
   {3x} &amp; 0 &amp; 2  \cr 
   {{x^2}} &amp; 2 &amp; 1  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x(2 - 1) - 0 + 2(2x - 2) + 3x(2 - 1) - 0 + 2({x^2} - 0) = 0$$ [expression w.r.t. first row]<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x + 4x - 4 + 3x + 2{x^2} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 2{x^2} + 8x - 4 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {x^2} + 4x - 2 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x = {{ - 4\, \pm \,\sqrt {16 - 4(1)( - 2)} } \over 2}$$<br><br>$$ = {{ - 4\, \pm \sqrt {24} } \over 2} = {{ - 4\, \pm 2\sqrt 6 } \over 2}$$<br><br>$$ =  - 2\, \pm \sqrt 6 $$

